ud5.5:17.2:
The fact that the ocean is the abode of such mighty beings as these:
whales, whale-eaters, & whale-eater-eaters;
asuras, nāgas, & gandhabbas;
and there are in the ocean beings one hundred leagues long,
two hundred… three hundred… four hundred… five hundred leagues long:

ud5.5:26.1:
[8] And furthermore, just as the ocean is the abode of such mighty beings as these:
whales, whale-eaters, & whale-eater-eaters;
asuras, nāgas, & gandhabbas, and there are in the ocean beings one hundred leagues long,
two hundred… three hundred… four hundred… five hundred leagues long;

ud5.5:26.2:
in the same way, this Dhamma & Vinaya is the abode of such mighty beings as these:
stream-winners & those practicing to realize the fruit of stream-entry;
once-returners & those practicing to realize the fruit of once-returning;
non-returners & those practicing to realize the fruit of non-returning;
arahants & those practicing for arahantship.

